@startuml
title Note Write And Mixed Write

actor User
participant Runtime
participant "Memory API" as API
participant Router
participant Retriever
participant "Entity Canonicalizer" as Canon
participant "Note Constructor" as NConstruct
participant "Note Reconciler" as NRecon
participant "Claim Extractor" as CExtract
participant "Claim Reconciler" as CRecon
participant "Task Updater" as TUpdate
participant "Profile Updater" as PUpdate
database DB

User -> Runtime: Rationale / design discussion / mixed turn
Runtime -> API: persist_source(turn)
API -> DB: INSERT Source

Runtime -> API: process_memory_write(source_id)
API -> Router: route(latest_turns)
Router --> API: note_write or mixed

API -> Retriever: retrieve_for_update\n(notes, claims, tasks, profile, sources)
Retriever -> DB: SELECT candidate items
Retriever --> API: candidate memory pack

API -> Canon: canonicalize_entities(turn, candidates)
Canon --> API: resolved entities

alt note_write
    API -> NConstruct: construct_notes(turn, entities,\nretrieved notes, sources)
    NConstruct --> API: candidate notes
    API -> NRecon: reconcile_notes(candidates,\nexisting notes)
    NRecon --> API: note ops
    API -> DB: APPLY note transaction\n(notes, links, lineage)
else mixed
    API -> NConstruct: construct_notes(...)
    NConstruct --> API: candidate notes
    API -> NRecon: reconcile_notes(...)
    NRecon --> API: note ops

    API -> CExtract: extract_claims(turn, entities,\npredicate_catalog)
    CExtract --> API: candidate claims
    API -> CRecon: reconcile_claims(candidates,\nexisting claims)
    CRecon --> API: claim ops

    API -> TUpdate: update_tasks(turn, existing tasks)
    TUpdate --> API: task ops

    API -> PUpdate: rebuild_profile(...)
    PUpdate --> API: profile projection

    API -> DB: APPLY mixed transaction\n(note ops + structured ops + lineage)
end

API -> DB: INSERT MemoryRun
API --> Runtime: write complete

note over NConstruct, NRecon
Notes capture rationale, direction, and evolving plans
without forcing premature hard facts.
end note

@enduml
